Type
species: 

Penthimia fulviventris
Walker, 1851

, by original designation.

subSubSection.paragraph:
Forewings (
Fig. 12B
) generally covered with several hair clusters or not, valvate behind clavus which’s apex truncate, claval suture obviously folded downward, venation somewhat prominent, largely obscured by opaque sclerotization and bushy hair cluster in basal 2/3, vein RA1 somewhat weak or absent, veins Pcu and A1 separated from each other, three anteapical cells, central anteapical cell slightly longer than outer and inner anteapical cells, four to five apical cells, 3rd apical cell usually shortest, appendix well developed and with numerous longitudinal crenulae, extended around wing apex from claval suture to 4th apical cell.
